  02 Apr 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org> -xalan-2.6.0-r1.ebuild,
  xalan-2.6.0-r2.ebuild:
  cleanup, removed old revision with a dependency to regexp.

*xalan-2.6.0-r2 (27 Mar 2005)

  27 Mar 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org> +xalan-2.6.0-r2.ebuild:
  moved from dev-java/regexp to dev-java/jakarta-regexp dependency, see #71336.
  keyworded ~amd64 and introduced support for the jikes and source useflag.

  26 Jan 2005; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> xalan-2.6.0-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64

  18 Dec 2004; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> xalan-2.6.0-r1.ebuild:
  added ~ppc64 to KEYWORDS

  28 Oct 2004; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> xalan-2.6.0-r1.ebuild:
  Added ~sparc keyword.

  17 Oct 2004; Dylan Carlson <absinthe@gentoo.org> xalan-2.6.0.ebuild
  keywords amd64.

  16 Oct 2004; Thomas Matthijs <axxo@gentoo.org> xalan-2.5.2.ebuild,
  xalan-2.6.0-r1.ebuild, xalan-2.6.0.ebuild:
  use java-pkg_dohtml instead of dohtml to also install the package-list in
  case of api docs: #50740

  04 Oct 2004; <SeJo@gentoo.org> xalan-2.6.0.ebuild:
  stable on ppc

  27 Sep 2004; Thomas Matthijs <axxo@gentoo.org> xalan-2.6.0-r1.ebuild:
  small dep fix

*xalan-2.6.0-r1 (19 Sep 2004)

  19 Sep 2004; Thomas Matthijs <axxo@gentoo.org> +xalan-2.6.0-r1.ebuild:
  no longer uses packed jars, also removed the ugly doc building hack, and made
  it use premade ones from apache, its not worth the trouble imo, feel free to
  supply patches to bugs.g.o & shoot me if you believe otherwise

  11 Sep 2004; Daniel Ahlberg <aliz@gentoo.org> xalan-2.6.0.ebuild:
  Added amd64 keyword, closing #59279.

